Female subgenital plate (
Fig. 64
): Less rectangular than usual, posterior margin rounded and sometimes slightly overhanging the segment. Antero-lateral recess usually distinct, the plate is entirely brown; lateral sclerites relatively large.

Distribution and ecology. The species is found in southern Slovakia , northeastern Hungary , northern and central Serbia . Specimens from Austria and Germany are attributed to this species on the basis of morphology ( Figs. 196–197 ). Adults were found in March emerging from slow or moderately fast flowing, large to mediumsized streams, mostly in alder (
Alnus glutinosa Gaertin.
) forests, but also in open grasslands between 200– 1,000m ( Fig. 193 ).
